<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Justin Bieber recently caused some controversy when he broke social distancing guidelines to throw a party at his Beverly Hills mansion.</p>

<p>But the Grammy winner has since gotten out of the city, boarding a private jet with wife Hailey over the weekend.</p>

<p>He and Hailey got down and dirty Monday, as they rode ATVs in the mountains with friends, while promoting his streetwear merch line Drew House.</p>

<p>Down and dirty: Justin Bieber and wife Hailey got down and dirty Monday, as they rode ATVs in the mountains with friends, while promoting his streetwear merch line Drew House</p>

<p>The 26-year-old posted a photo to Instagram of himself standing next to Hailey, 23, who sat on an ATV, both of them covered in dirt.</p>

<p>He captioned the photo of his bride giving him a stink eye: 'Hailey : “what did you get me into Justin”'</p>

<p>Justin sported a black hoodie and matching sweatpants with a grey t-shirt and a black smiley face beanie, all from his collection, finished with some groovy yellow rectangular sunglasses.</p>

<p>Hailey donned a lilac Drew House sweatsuit, accessorized with gold earrings, matching necklaces and a pair of thick blue riding goggles.</p>

<p>Cute: Justin posted a playful photo of he and wife Hailey </p>

<p>Sponcon: They appeared to be promoting the brand, as Justin later took to his Instagram Story with a video of his friend in some merch</p>

<p>Gorgeous view: The Yummy artist zoomed in and out of the Drew House logos on his friend's black cotton shorts and brown trucker hat, while standing in front of a scenic mountain vista</p>

<p>Jetset life: It comes after he and Hailey boarded a private jet to escape Los Angeles over the weekend</p>

<p>They appeared to be promoting the brand, as Justin later took to his Instagram Story with a video of his friend in some merch.</p>

<p>The Yummy artist zoomed in and out of the Drew House logos on his friend's black cotton shorts and brown trucker hat, while standing in front of a scenic mountain vista. </p>

<p>He was previously spotted arriving last week at the brand's Los Angeles headquarters for what appeared to be a video shoot.</p>

<p>Justin took precautions against COVID-19, as he had his temperature taken at a security checkpoint outside the entrance. </p>

<p>He wasn't as careful the weekend before, as he and Hailey hosted a star-studded party at their Beverly Hills mansion.</p>

<p>Hard at work: He was previously spotted arriving last week at the brand's Los Angeles headquarters for what appeared to be a video shoot</p>

<p>Dangerous party: Justin and Hailey broke social distancing guidelines last weekend to host a star-studded party at their Beverly Hills mansion</p>

<p>Rule breakers: It comes after the Los Angeles Department of Public Health released guidelines earlier this month that stated: 'Individual and family gatherings or parties of any size aren’t allowed'</p>

<p>They threw a huge bash last Sunday at their $8.5million abode, attended by celeb pals like Hudson, Jaden Smith, Winnie Harlow, Kendall and Kylie Jenner.</p>

<p>Guests were spotted gathering outside the 6,132-square-foot Monterey Colonial home, none of them wearing face masks. </p>

<p>It comes after the Los Angeles Department of Public Health released guidelines earlier this month that stated: 'Individual and family gatherings or parties of any size aren’t allowed.'</p>

<p>Mayor Eric Garcetti has since advised the city to cut off utility supplies to properties holding such gatherings. </p>

<p>Bryce Hall's Sway House and other TikTok 'content houses' have recently faced this punishment for recently hosting massive house parties in the Hollywood Hills.</p>

<p>Justin and Hailey have since dropped $25.8million on a new party pad, snatching up a 11,145-square-foot, seven-bedroom, 10-bathroom mansion in the nearby gated community of Beverly Park.</p>

